{"root":{"data":{"text":"Literature Review on M. rosenbergii Research"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"I. Aquaculture Optimization & Growth Regulation","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"1. Photoperiod Regulation (Wang, 2025)","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"Finding: Extended photoperiod (L24:D0) promotes molting and enhances early growth performance (survival, weight gain) in juvenile prawns.","layout":null},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"Evaluation: Future studies should extend to other tissues (e.g. nervous system) to fully understand photoperiodic signaling.","layout":null},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"2. Feed Nutrition Innovation (Chen, 2025)","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"Finding: Defatted black soldier fly larvae meal (BSFLM) is a viable fishmeal substitute in prawn diets.","layout":null},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"Evaluation: Research needed on long-term effects, cost-effectiveness, and validation across farming models.","layout":null},"children":[]}]}]},{"data":{"text":"II. Disease Control & Health Management","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"1. Bacterial Infection & Gut Health (Tang, 2025)","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"Finding: Vibrio infection causes intestinal dysbiosis, impairs barrier function, and damages tissue in prawns.","layout":null},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"Evaluation: Findings require validation across different farming models and geographical regions.","layout":null},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"2. Novel Antiviral Strategy (Chantunmapitak, 2025)","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"Finding: Engineered a novel antiviral strategy against M. rosenbergii nodavirus (MrNV) based on viral capsid engineering and glycan recognition.","layout":null},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"Evaluation: Integrates structural biology and glycobiology, offering a new paradigm for antiviral design.","layout":null},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"3. Probiotic Application (Mahfuz, 2025)","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"Finding: Host-derived probiotics are a highly effective and species-specific alternative for sustainable prawn aquaculture.","layout":null},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"Evaluation: The specific biological mechanisms behind this effect require further in-depth exploration.","layout":null},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"4. Immune System Review (Kumaresan, 2016)","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"Finding: Systematically consolidates knowledge on the immune system of M. rosenbergii and summarizes immunoenhancement strategies.","layout":null},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"Evaluation: Integrates scattered research and offers clear practical guidance.","layout":null},"children":[]}]}]},{"data":{"text":"III. Food Safety & Detection Technology","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"1. Enzymology & Preservation (Sriket, 2012)","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"Finding: First report of a low molecular weight (17 kDa) trypsin from the hepatopancreas of M. rosenbergii in crustaceans.","layout":null},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"Evaluation: Provides key evidence for understanding spoilage mechanisms at the molecular level, laying a foundation for preservation techniques.","layout":null},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"2. Drug Residue Detection (Van Poucke et al., 2011)","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"Finding: Semicarbazide (SEM) is not a reliable marker for nitrofurazone misuse; alternative detection methods are needed.","layout":null},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"Evaluation: Highlights the limitations of SEM as a marker and promotes refinement of related detection standards.","layout":null},"children":[]}]}]},{"data":{"text":"IV. Environmental Stress & Biomarkers","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"1. Heavy Metal Response & MT Gene Expression (Mahmood et al., 2009)","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"Finding: The metallothionein gene Mar-MT-1 shows distinct expression patterns under exposure to Cd, Cu, Zn, and thermal stress.","layout":null},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"Evaluation: Systematically reveals MT gene regulation characteristics, holding significant reference value for heavy metal biomonitoring.","layout":null},"children":[]}]}]},{"data":{"text":"V. Genetic Resources & Breeding Tools","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"1. Microsatellite Marker Development (Divu et al., 2008)","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"Finding: Isolated and characterized eight polymorphic microsatellite markers from M. rosenbergii via a microsatellite-enriched library.","layout":null},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"Evaluation: Systematically established a development and validation pipeline, filling the gap in high-throughput genetic markers for this species.","layout":null},"children":[]}]}]},{"data":{"text":"VI. Research Trends & Future Directions","layout":null},"children":[{"data":{"text":"Shift from single-factor to multi-stress and combined-pollution studies.","layout":null},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"Increased integration of molecular, structural, and computational biology.","layout":null},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"Focus on species-specific mechanisms and practical, sustainable solutions.","layout":null},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"Need for cross-regional, cross-model validation of findings.","layout":null},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"Development of novel biomarkers and high-throughput genetic tools.","layout":null},"children":[]}]}]},"template":"right","theme":"fresh-blue-compat","version":"1.4.43"}